              "displayName": "Steve Loughran",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Europe/London"
            },
            "body": "+1 to this idea -without it AMs can't track topologies that change over time.\n\nThis should include\n# failure domain topology\n# time last updated\n\nHaving a timestamp will let the AMs decide whether or not to rebuild their local datastructures when querying the rack.\n\nActually, having a notification that the topology has changed could be even more useful for some applications, but that is very much feature creep.",
